ZH: 我每天晚上都会温习功课。
EN: I review my homework every night.

ZH: 她是一个很勤奋的学生，总是喜欢温习复习。
EN: She is a diligent student who always likes to review.

ZH: 在考试前，我会花很多时间来温习。
EN: I spend a lot of time reviewing before exams.

ZH: 学生们应该养成每天温习的好习惯。
EN: Students should develop a habit of reviewing every day.

ZH: 老师建议我们多花时间温习语法知识。
EN: The teacher suggests that we spend more time reviewing grammar.

ZH: 我发现温习对记忆很有帮助。
EN: I find that reviewing is very helpful for memory.

ZH: 温习不一定要在书桌前进行，可以利用碎片时间。
EN: Reviewing doesn't have to be done at a desk, it can be done in spare time.

ZH: 我通常在公交车上温习生词。
EN: I usually review new words on the bus.

ZH: 他经常在晚饭后温习发音。
EN: He often reviews pronunciation after dinner.

ZH: 她在准备考试时会花很多时间温习历史知识。
EN: She spends a lot of time reviewing history knowledge when preparing for exams.

ZH: 我们小组的任务是温习课本上的内容。
EN: Our group's task is to review the content in the textbook.

ZH: 温习和理解是学习过程中的两个重要环节。
EN: Reviewing and understanding are two important stages in the learning process.

ZH: 他建议我们结合温习和练习来更好地掌握知识。
EN: He suggests that we combine reviewing and practice to better master knowledge.

ZH: 她喜欢通过回答问题来温习学过的知识。
EN: She likes to review the knowledge she has learned by answering questions.

ZH: 在复习的过程中，我经常发现自己还有哪些知识没有掌握。
EN: During the process of review, I often find which knowledge I have not yet mastered.

ZH: 温习需要有计划、有目的。
EN: Reviewing needs to be planned and purposeful.

ZH: 他很努力，每天都在温习以便考试顺利。
EN: He works hard, reviewing every day to ensure a smooth exam.

ZH: 成功的关键之一是不断温习，不断进步。
EN: One of the keys to success is constant review and progress.

ZH: 温习是我们巩固知识的有效方法之一。
EN: Reviewing is one of the effective methods for us to consolidate knowledge.
